parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Pressure Loss
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of oil pressure can cause the engine to seize, leading to catastrophic failure, stalling, and loss of control, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the oil pump can cause the engine to lose oil pressure, leading to engine failure, stalling, and loss of control, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the engine bearings can cause the engine to seize, leading to catastrophic failure, stalling, and loss of control, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Improperly Installed Fuel Filler Tube Gaskets
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water can enter the left rear quarter panel, causing the steering electronics to short out, leading to a loss of power steering without warning, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: water entry into the left rear quarter panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose Lower Control Arms and Ball Joints
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose control arms and ball joints can cause a loss of steering control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Creaking noise in the front suspension when turning the steering wheel
especially when parked or at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Power Steering Failure

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the passenger restraint system can lead to inadequate protection in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to passengers.
